==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*hamara-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[hamar]]'' (Dutch ''[[hamer]]''), Old High German ''[[hamar]]'' (German ''[[Hammer]]''), Old Norse ''[[hamarr]]'' (Swedish ''[[hammare]]'').

